`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"When I talk about SLMs, I'm talking about the smaller, lighter versions of big language models. They're compact, fast, and cheap to run, but still surprisingly capable. Because they don't need massive cloud compute, they're great for things like edge devices, personal assistants, or any use case where privacy matters. They're basically a practical way to get a lot of AI power without the huge overhead."}),`
